# Private npm registry for the @yottagraph-app/* scope.
#
# These packages are served ONLY from the org's GCP Artifact Registry, never
# public npmjs. This scope-pin is the keystone dependency-confusion control:
# npm will never resolve @yottagraph-app/* from the public registry, so a
# same-named public package cannot be substituted into any build here.
#
# Auth is by GCP IAM (roles/artifactregistry.reader on broadchurch/aether-npm).
# Set AR_NPM_TOKEN to a short-lived OAuth access token before installing, e.g.
#   export AR_NPM_TOKEN="$(gcloud auth print-access-token)"
# In GitHub Actions the workflows mint it via Workload Identity Federation.
# If AR_NPM_TOKEN is unset, installs of @yottagraph-app/* fail closed (401) —
# they do NOT silently fall back to public npm.
#
# See broadchurch/docs/NPM_PRIVATE_REGISTRY.md for the full setup + runbook.
@yottagraph-app:registry=https://us-central1-npm.pkg.dev/broadchurch/aether-npm/
//us-central1-npm.pkg.dev/broadchurch/aether-npm/:_authToken=${AR_NPM_TOKEN}
